13.Sete de Setembro   26   3   9  14  33-48  15  Relegated [1]
14.Meridional         26   4   5  17  29-59  13  Relegated

[1] Sete de Setembro won the points of one of their defeats against Renascenea
because the latter fielded an irregular player. Therefore, Renascenea was forced
to play a tiebreak with Bela Vista in order to decide who would remain in the top
flight and who would play-off against Itae for a spot in the top division.

Tiebreak playoffs (at neutral venues):
[May 13, 1962]
Renascenea   2-3   Bela Vista   [at America]

[May 17]
Bela Vista   1-4   Renascenea   [at Atletico]

[May 19]
Renascenea   2-0   Bela Vista   [at Sete de Setembro]

Renascenea remained in Extra Division. Bela Vista qualified for the relegation playoff
against Itae, champions of 1961 First Division.

Relegation playoffs:
(Itae played leg 1 home)

[Jun 3 and 10, 1962]
Itae   1-0   0-2   Bela Vista

Tiebreak (neutral venue):
[Jun 13]
Bela Vista   2-2   Itae    [at America]  [0-0 a.e.t.]

Bela Vista remained in Extra Division due to better goal difference in the three matches.

*** CRUZEIRO are Minas Gerais State Champions of 1961 ***

Topscorers: Amauri (America), Rossi (Cruzeiro) and Gilberto (Pedro Leopoldo) - 14 goals

